				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Raisa wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Whats better to get the horse or that wierd lizard thing? I guess since I dont ever think Ill have enough money to get the best horse I need to just get the cheapest horse to have the ability to med without sitting.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
My gnome mage bought a horse before LoY was released and Dogmars {sp} were introduced.  Actually, for a gnome, you get a pony, not a horse as the size of the horse/Dogmor is based on the size of the PC race.  With my gnome, I never had much problems targeting things.  I also have a Dwarf Cleric I two box.  I bought him a horse.  Dwarfs are not that much bigger than Gnomes, but the difference on reduction of targeting area because of the larger horse head is extreme.  
<br />

<br />
Because the Dogmars head is so low, it does not have the "targeting problems" a horse head.   There is not functional reason to have a horse over a Dogmar, it purely asthetics.  I think Gnome's on pony's look cooler that Gnomes on Dogmars.  But, if you are a larger race and you target things with you mouse often, you need to choose a Dogmar for UI reasons.  If my Dwarf cleric needed to target things with the mouse, I would sell his horse and get a Dogmar.  But mostly the cleric's uses the Target Group member keys to target so I don't find it a large problem.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
<br />
